9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1145, L.D. 1710, “An Act Regarding
10 the Authority to Transport Prisoners Confined in Jail and the Use of Physical Force with
11 Respect to Prisoners and Persons Who Have Been Arrested”
12 Amend the bill in section 5 in §107-A by inserting after subsection 4 the following:
13 '5. Notwithstanding any provision of this section to the contrary, a corrections officer
14 or corrections supervisor is not justified in using nondeadly or deadly force, or in directing
15 a private person in the use of such force, in accordance with this section unless the
16 corrections officer or corrections supervisor has received in-service training pursuant to
17 Title 25, section 2804-F, subsection 5 in the use of such force, or in directing a private
18 person to use such force, in the setting in which the force is to be used.'
19 Amend the bill by inserting after section 8 the following:
20 'Sec. 9. 25 MRSA §2804-F, sub-§3, as amended by PL 2013, c. 147, §35, is further
21 amended to read:
22 3. Provisions of in-service training. In-service training programs that meet the
23 requirements established under subsection 2 or 5 or other in-service training may be
24 provided by the Maine Criminal Justice Academy or the agency employing the corrections
25 officer.
26 Sec. 10. 25 MRSA §2804-F, sub-§5 is enacted to read:
27 5. Additional certifications. The board shall establish additional in-service training
28 requirements for corrections officers and corrections supervisors who are responsible as
29 part of their official job duties for transferring or conveying from one place to another
30 individuals who are confined in a jail, prison or state correctional facility pursuant to an
31 order of a court or as a result of an arrest. These in-service training requirements must
32 include training on the use of nondeadly or deadly force, or in directing a private person in
33 the use of such force, that is used or directed outside of a jail, prison or state correctional
34 facility. A corrections officer or corrections supervisor who fails to complete this in-service
