3 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
4 number to read consecutively.
5 SUMMARY
66 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, amends the bill by
77 requiring that the Board of Trustees of the Maine Criminal Justice Academy establish
88 additional in-service training requirements for corrections officers and corrections
99 supervisors who are responsible as part of their official job duties for transferring or
1100 conveying from one place to another individuals who are confined in a jail, prison or state
1111 correctional facility pursuant to an order of a court or as a result of an arrest. The in-service
1122 training must include training on the use of nondeadly or deadly force, or in directing a
1133 private person in the use of such force, that is used or directed outside of a jail, prison or
1144 state correctional facility. If a corrections officer or corrections supervisor does not
1155 complete this additional training, the corrections officer or corrections supervisor is not
1166 justified in the use or direction of such force. This training may be provided by the Maine
1177 Criminal Justice Academy or the agency employing the corrections officer or corrections
1188 supervisor.
